{"key":"post-9982059","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9982059</id>\n<content>You only use lime in the water bath for &lt;i&gt;pasteurizing straw&lt;/i&gt;, and then it drains off with the water.&amp;nbsp; Don't lime bulk substrates such as manure or coir, paper, woodchips, sawdust, etc.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The pulp you found will probably work OK for oysters, but why pay for what you can get free?&amp;nbsp; Just use old newspapers, cardboard, magazines, etc., that you have laying around or can get from neighbors.&amp;nbsp; My county government recently gave me the key to the recycling bins so I can get newsprint and other paper products anytime I want for free.&amp;nbsp; Sometimes all you have to do is ask.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To correct your nomenclature, spawn consists of the cakes or grains you use to start/expand your mycelium.&amp;nbsp; The paper would be your bulk substrate.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-40/135930560-Phone_Book_Shiitake_013a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-40/135930560-thumb_Phone_Book_Shiitake_013a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-40/135930550-Phone_Book_Oyster_006a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-40/135930550-thumb_Phone_Book_Oyster_006a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-34/787406648-phonebook_hericium_029a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/t